HEADWORD: Oscillating current
<hw>Os"cil*lat`ing current</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A current
alternating in direction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oscillating engine</b></col>, <cd>a steam engine whose
cylinder oscillates on trunnions instead of being permanently fixed in a
perpendicular or other direction.</cd> <rj><au>Weale.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oscillation</ent>⟦br⟧
